{{Geology to Paleobiology}}
A geologic '''age''' is a subdivision of [[geologic time]] that divides an [[Epoch (geology)|epoch]] into smaller parts. A [[Geologic record|succession of rock strata]] laid down in a single age on the [[geologic timescale]] is a [[Stage (stratigraphy)|stage]].

