'''Alan Allport''' (born 1970) is a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[historian]] whose work looks at the relationship between war and society during the period of the two world wars. He was born in [[Whiston, Merseyside|Whiston]], [[Merseyside]] and moved to the United States in 1994. Allport received a [[Ph.D.]] in history from the [[University of Pennsylvania]] in 2007 and currently teaches at [[Syracuse University]]. His first book ''Demobbed: Coming Home After the Second World War'', a study of the post-1945 military [[Demobilization of the British Armed Forces after World War II|demobilisation]] experience in Britain, was published by [[Yale University Press]] in 2009 and won the 2010 [[Longman-History Today Awards|Longman-''History Today'' Book of the Year Award]].<ref>http://www.historytoday.com/awards {{webarchive |url=https://www.webcitation.org/5wIqFtkYC?url=http://www.historytoday.com/awards |date=February 6, 2011 }}</ref> His second book, ''Browned Off and Bloody-Minded: The British Soldier goes to War 1939-1945'' was published, also by Yale, in 2015.
